"AI isn't real" is about coherent of a take as "data science is fake" 

Most people who actually have to code ML aren't under serious delusions about exactly what AI consists of—algorithms on large datasets.

Any delusional claims about AI are usually from people outside related fields. Inside the world, usually at worst you get a Godel-Escher-Bach-ian concerning what can and cannot emerge from algorithms. Which is a fairly legitimate discussion.
